        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 1:24AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 123 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Kennedy, or near Millport, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northport, Fayette, Vernon, Gordo, Reform, Millport, Berry, Kennedy,
Belk, Ethelsville, Bankston, Samantha, Lake Lurleen State Park,
Ashcraft Corner, Boley Springs, Deerlick Creek Campgrounds, Binion
Creek Landing, Crossville, Cody, and Lake Tuscaloosa.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
